{"parse":{"title":"Geoffrey the Monk","pageid":58384852,"revid":858758737,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Geoffrey the Monk</b> was the count of Marash in the <a href=\"/wiki/Principality_of_Antioch\" title=\"Principality of Antioch\">Principality of Antioch</a> (now <a href=\"/wiki/Kahramanmara%C5%9F\" title=\"Kahramanmara\u015f\">Kahramanmara\u015f</a>, Turkey) from around 1114 to 1124.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Count_of_Marash\">Count of Marash</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Geoffrey_the_Monk&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Count of Marash\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The first reference to Geoffrey was connected to his participation in the <a href=\"/wiki/Battle_of_Ager_Sanguinis\" title=\"Battle of Ager Sanguinis\">Battle of the \"Field of Blood\"</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000162_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000162-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> In this battle, Ilghazi, the <a href=\"/wiki/Artuqids\" title=\"Artuqids\">Artuqid</a> ruler of <a href=\"/wiki/Mardin\" title=\"Mardin\">Mardin</a> almost annihilated the army of <a href=\"/wiki/Roger_of_Salerno\" title=\"Roger of Salerno\">Roger of Salerno</a>, the ruler of Antioch on 28 June, 1119.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000162_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000162-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> According to the 12th-century historian <a href=\"/wiki/William_of_Tyre\" title=\"William of Tyre\">William of Tyre</a>, Geoffrey and Guy Fresnel jointly commanded a battle-line.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000172_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000172-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Geoffrey managed to escape from the battlefield after Ilghazi's victory.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000162_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000162-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> William of Tyre described Geoffrey as a \"magnate of the region\", without specifying his title.<sup id=\"cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBuck2017134_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-FOOTNOTEBuck2017134-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Geoffrey_the_Monk&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000162-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000162_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000162_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000162_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFAsbridge2000\">Asbridge 2000</a>, p.&#160;162.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000172-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEAsbridge2000172_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFAsbridge2000\">Asbridge 2000</a>, p.&#160;172.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-FOOTNOTEBuck2017134-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-FOOTNOTEBuck2017134_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"#CITEREFBuck2017\">Buck 2017</a>, p.&#160;134.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sources\">Sources</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Geoffrey_the_Monk&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Sources\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsec